olive oil
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
1 packet Pork Scotch Fillet
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tbs soy sauce
3 cup water
2 egg
1 packet Egg Noodles
1 packet Asian Greens

• Thinly slice carrot into rounds. Finely chop garlic. Cut pork scotch fillet into 3cm chunks and season generously with salt and pepper.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook pork until browned on all sides, 3-4 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium, add garlic, sweet soy seasoning and ginger paste, and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add teriyaki sauce, carrot, chicken-style stock powder, the soy sauce and water, and stir to combine. Transfer to slow cooker and set cooking temperature to high.
• Place lid on slow cooker and cook, stirring each hour, until pork falls apart, 4 hours.

TIP: If you don't have a slow cooker, preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced. Transfer mixture to an ovenproof saucepan, cover with lid (or tightly with foil) and bake until pork is tender, 90 minutes.

• When the pork has 20 minutes remaining, boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Cook the eggs in boiling water, over high heat, until soft-boiled, 7 minutes. Using tongs, remove eggs from saucepan and cool in cold water. Peel and halve.

• When the eggs are done, return saucepan to high heat and bring back to the boil. Cook egg noodles, stirring occasionally with a fork to separate, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Drain, rinse and divide between serving bowls.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop Asian greens.
• When the pork has 5 minutes remaining, add Asian greens to slow cooker. Stir until wilted.

• Pour slow cooked pork ramen over egg noodles.
• Top with soft boiled eggs to serve. Enjoy!